course: main course
servings: 2
---

Boil a full #kettle{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, lay the @Serrano ham{2%slices} into the pan and fry until crispy, ~{2-3%minutes} each side. Once crispy, transfer to a plate covered in #kitchen paper{}. Set aside.

Put the frying pan back on high heat with a generous drizzle of @oil{}.

When hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{120%g} to the pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and fry, stirring occasionally, until browned, ~{6-8%minutes}.

While the mushrooms are frying, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Once the mushrooms have browned, add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @tomato passata{1%carton}, @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @vegan 'Nduja{1/2%sachet} (see ingredients for amount, use less if you'd prefer things milder), @sugar{1%tsp} and @water{50%ml} for the sauce (see pantry for both amounts).

> This 'Nduja is completely meat-free but with all the same flavour, featuring a hot, umami blend of Calabrian chillies and peppers.

Simmer the sauce until thickened slightly, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pour the boiled water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/2%tsp} and bring back to the boil.

Add the @Parma Ham & Parmigiano Reggiano Filled Pasta{250%g} and cook until tender, ~{3%minutes}.

Once cooked, carefully drain in a #colander{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and gently stir through to stop it sticking together.

Once your sauce has thickened, stir the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{20%g} through the sauce until melted.

Remove from the heat.

Taste and season with more salt, pepper and sugar to taste.

Gently stir your filled pasta through the sauce and share between your #serving bowls{}.

Snap the Serrano into shards.

Top with the @wild rocket{20%g}, Serrano shards and drizzle some @olive oil{} over the leaves to finish. Enjoy!